      'projects.tipe.title':    'Shape Optimization of a Flywheel',
      'projects.tipe.desc':     'Maximize the moment of inertia of a flywheel under a fixed perimeter constraint. Four parameterizations compared (Fourier, Polynomial, Polar, 3D extension) using L-BFGS-B and Trust-Region solvers. Convergence to the circle confirmed analytically via the isoperimetric inequality. Validated experimentally on a 34g miniature vehicle with 1.8%–5.7% velocity error.',
      'projects.thepnlab.num':  '02 — ThePnLab · Live',
      'projects.thepnlab.title': 'Algorithmic Paper Trading Platform',
      'projects.thepnlab.desc': 'Free paper-trading simulation platform for French students. A multi-criteria decision engine (TOPSIS on 50+ assets) selects positions daily; Kelly Criterion sizes them; a VIX regime controller scales exposure. 40-day baseline shows +0.00% bot PnL vs −5.02% human discretionary — behavioral divergence confirmed, edge not yet statistically significant.',
      'projects.amje.num':      '03 — AMJE Lille · Business Manager · Ongoing',
      'projects.amje.title':    'Missions & Projects',
      'projects.amje.desc':     'Junior-Entreprise of ENSAM Lille — real missions for real clients. <strong>TourniMap:</strong> VRP heuristics for 650 retail points (K-Means++, 2-opt, OSRM API), deployed on GitHub Pages. <strong>Commercial strategy:</strong> 286 prospects → 7 signed engagements, funnel decomposition, bottleneck at qualification stage (14.7%). €30,000 revenue last year, +33% growth projected.',
      'projects.cnn.num':       '04 — LISPEN · Starting April 2026',
      'projects.cnn.title':     'Predictive Maintenance & Optimal Threshold',
      'projects.cnn.desc':      'PJT1A group project starting end of April 2026. CNN on mel-spectrograms (CWRU bearings dataset) for fault classification. Personal OR extension: find threshold θ* minimising expected total cost = c_prev·P(false alarm) + c_failure·P(missed detection), subject to machine availability ≥ 95%. Potential research collaboration with LISPEN lab (ENSAM) — ongoing discussions.',
      'projects.fsam.num':      '05 — FSAM · In Progress · FS Spain & Germany',
      'projects.fsam.title':    'Formula Student — ENSAM Lille',
      'projects.fsam.desc':     'Project management and technical support on ENSAM Lille\'s Formula Student team. Responsible for the full vehicle Bill of Materials (18+ assemblies, Excel + 3DExperience), stock management, and cross-team coordination toward competition.',
      'projects.pwc.num':       '06 — PwC VivaTech · Submitted · Awaiting results',
